1
00:00:03,031 --> 00:00:06,134
The 737 MAX was sold as a familiar airplane.

2
00:00:06,915 --> 00:00:08,177
That was the commercial promise.

3
00:00:09,099 --> 00:00:13,826
Airlines could keep crews, schedules, and training close to the old 737.

4
00:00:14,567 --> 00:00:19,312
Then Boeing put larger CFM Leap engines on the aircraft.

5
00:00:20,254 --> 00:00:27,704
They sat farther forward and higher on the wing, and under certain high angle of attack conditions, the jet could pitch up differently.

6
00:00:28,207 --> 00:00:37,036
MCAS was built to make that new behavior feel familiar, but the system could move the stabilizer from one angle of attack sensor.

7
00:00:38,076 --> 00:00:40,840
Pilots were not clearly trained that it existed by name.

8
00:00:42,240 --> 00:00:48,707
After Lionair 610, the warning still was not reclassified fast enough as an architectural problem.

9
00:00:49,508 --> 00:00:50,628
The plane had changed.

10
00:00:51,590 --> 00:00:54,031
The story told to the people flying it had not.

11
00:00:54,832 --> 00:00:57,996
Small causes, massive consequences.
